Abdomen.
Abdomen with tenth tergite (
Fig. 5C
) well sclerotised, somewhat depressed in the middle; cercus very elongate, undulating, apex with a few teeth (
Fig. 5C
); subgenital plate broad, apex not especially narrowing, with a pair of short, style-like protuberances.

Abdomen.
Abdomen with tenth tergite prominent, well sclerotised, apex irregularly undulating; cercus (
Fig. 7C
) elongate, gently upcurved, apex blunt and with a pair of teeth; supra-anal plate apically divided; subgenital plate (
Fig. 7D
) short, stout, apex shallowly excavate, with a pair of short, peg-like protuberances.

